    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`sign` support allowed the GUI to place icons as defined through the `sign icon= command, but we have no equivalent for remote GUIs, and the old code got removed.\n\nPing equalsraf/neovim-qt#90.\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yeah, the old code was not something I think we'd want to bring over. Perhaps we can allow arbitrary msgpack objects to be stored on a sign? Then UIs can use them how they like. Plugins would need to use API calls to \"configure\" the signs; we don't want to extend the `:sign` command.\n",
